{
  "stem": "945.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, within a few days, we found out that hundreds and hundreds of families have been forced, in the middle of the night, into trucks and disappeared.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Were these Jewish families-- non-Jewish families?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mostly Jewish families, because Vishnitz was a Yiddish shtetl.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There may have been some non-Jewish families, as well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But where we lived it was mostly Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The people that were gone were some of our friends, some of our neighbors, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] local storekeepers, local butcher shops, local people that were professional, but didn't quite fit the communist mold.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Pardon me.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At first, we didn't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we soon learned that most of them were sent off to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was-- it's-- it's kind of the type of news that communicates out of-- from word to mouth.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and people do find out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I know, because one of those people was my Uncle Moyche, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] who was declared an enemy, simply because he lived in a large house and had a few trees of apples and-- and prunes and-- and things that grew in his own orchard.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he also, because he had a big house, and we lived on the outskirts of town, he had allowed to have a little synagogue in his house, so we could have-- so the Jewish people in that area could have prayers, Shabbos and Yontif.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And also, because a local official thought that maybe he'd like to have his house.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So one nice day, they asked them to come to the office, to this-- this country civil office.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they invited him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, he had no idea what it was for.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
